OL,3,CCare staff try 'fascinating' dementia
OL,4,Csuit to help them empathise with
OL,5,Cresidents
OL,7,F"Once I left the safety of my chair, I
OL,8,Fhad to concentrate on each step very
OL,9,Fcarefully as the weighted vest and
OL,10,Fankle straps almost threw me off
OL,11,Fbalance.
OL,13,F"I struggled to hear what Emma
OL,14,FCording, my trainer, was saying as she
OL,15,Fregularly checked in with me. But in
OL,16,Fmy headphones I had the equivalent of
OL,17,Ftinnitus ringing around my head.
OL,19,F"By the time I made it to the car, I
OL,20,Fwas mentally exhausted and I could
OL,21,Fbarely lift my feet.
